    {
      "id": "102539b75d23fad38e0647d0febf30f919defa9a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2019-10-20 18:21:42.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nPlease include Amir in all LNet patches. \n\nIt is great that you are adding additional LNet regression tests, since we are really lacking in this area. \n\nI see that the sanity-lnet test script is not new in this patch series. However, please note that just adding a script to the git repo doesn't mean that it will be run automatically. It needs to be added to one or more test sessions to ensure that the test is run for every patch and that the tests keep passing. That is why I suggested to put this into the existing lnet-selftest script, which is already being run. \n\nAlternately, please work with James N. to get this added to a test session.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "57f6db47f2fb4c498ebbd5cba52b12fe2b04de88",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 148,
        "name": "Chris Horn",
        "email": "chris.horn@hpe.com",
        "username": "hornc"
      },
      "date": "2019-10-20 18:24:52.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n> Please include Amir in all LNet patches.\n > \n > It is great that you are adding additional LNet regression tests,\n > since we are really lacking in this area.\n > \n > I see that the sanity-lnet test script is not new in this patch\n > series. However, please note that just adding a script to the git\n > repo doesn't mean that it will be run automatically. It needs to be\n > added to one or more test sessions to ensure that the test is run\n > for every patch and that the tests keep passing. That is why I\n > suggested to put this into the existing lnet-selftest script, which\n > is already being run.\n > \n > Alternately, please work with James N. to get this added to a test\n > session.\n\nsanity-lnet was previously added to lustre/tests/test-groups/regression\n\nIs that not sufficient?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "386c8684fe5186c728ed535f6dfa7c074fe00eae",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2019-10-20 22:53:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n> > Please include Amir in all LNet patches.\n > >\n > > It is great that you are adding additional LNet regression tests,\n > > since we are really lacking in this area.\n > >\n > > I see that the sanity-lnet test script is not new in this patch\n > > series. However, please note that just adding a script to the git\n > > repo doesn't mean that it will be run automatically. It needs to\n > be\n > > added to one or more test sessions to ensure that the test is run\n > > for every patch and that the tests keep passing. That is why I\n > > suggested to put this into the existing lnet-selftest script,\n > which\n > > is already being run.\n > >\n > > Alternately, please work with James N. to get this added to a\n > test\n > > session.\n > \n > sanity-lnet was previously added to lustre/tests/test-groups/regression\n > \n > Is that not sufficient?\n\nThat is the list of tests that are typically run when a developer does manual testing, but is not used for the automated tests run for patches in Gerrit.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "df6201b8be20a2b948bc00855cb8e3336149c24b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2019-10-21 06:23:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n> That is the list of tests that are typically run when a developer\n > does manual testing, but is not used for the automated tests run\n > for patches in Gerrit.\n\nThe list of sanity-lnet runs can be seen with the following search:\n\nhttps://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/query?utf8=%E2%9C%93&warn%5Bnotice%5D=&test_set_script_id=a2b1c4b2-b449-11e9-b88c-52540065bddc&horizon=2332800&&commit=Update+results\n\nThis shows it has been run 11 times, only as custom test runs when requested on the Test-Parameters: line for a patch.  We can and should add this into the regular test sessions, but I didn't even know that this script existed.\n\nJames N. can submit a patch for our test system to add this to a test session, maybe in the same places that lnet-selftest is run?  It only takes about 10 minutes to run.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "2ac647ffd3e85d2f23355c9cad69cc980cd20a0d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 292,
